question: 賃貸
partsOfSpeech: noun, する verb, の adjective
sourceMnemonic: <kanji>Rent</kanji> it and I will <kanji>lend</kanji> it to you. This thing that is being lent and rented? It's a <vocabulary>rental</vocabulary>.
sourceReadingMnemonic: This is a jukugo word that uses the on'yomi readings of the kanji. You just have to remember that <ja>貸</ja> is read as <ja>たい</ja> for this one. What is your rental? It is a <reading>tie</reading> (<ja>たい</ja>) fighter. Sweet.
